guangdong exports us $ 3.76 billion worth of high technology products in the first two months of this year
xinhua news agency report of march 16 from guangzhou ( by staff reporter chen ji ) - latest statistics indicate guangdong province exported us $ 3.76 billion worth of high technology products , up 34.8 percent from the same period last year , which account for 25.5 percent of the total exports of the province .
high technology product export registers positive signs and makes great contribution to guangdong 's foreign trade growth .
last year , guangdong province exported us $ 22.294 billion worth of high technology products , up 31 percent over the previous year and 27.2 percentage points higher than average export growth rate of the province ; the net increase of high technology export amounted to us $ 5.27 billion , making good the export decrease in consequence of the price cuts of the traditional labor-intensive products .
computers and telecommunication technology products stand out among guangdong 's high technology product exports , with a value of us $ 19.14 billion , or 85.9 percent of the total value .
the major target markets of guangdong 's high technology products are hong kong , united states , the european union and japan .
last year , exported products from the pearl river delta new and high technology industrial zone amounted to us21.99 billion , or 98.7 percent of the total value of high technology product export of the province .
the leading role of this area remains conspicuous this year .
at present , more than 95 percent of computer components are supplied locally in the pearl river delta area which is capable of providing all computer parts and components other than cpus .
fifa to punish cheating on soccer pitch
xinhua news agency report of march 17 from beijing - the executive committee of fifa disclosed on 16th at a meeting in switzerland that referees will take a tougher line in this year 's world cup against soccer players who attempt to gain by simulation such as divings .
according to foreign news reports , the executive committee of fifa expressed its backing in a news release for the referees to strictly enforce rules , particularly against players who cheat on the spectators .
the executive committee also announced some reform measures .
players will be allowed to take off their team shirts in celebration of goals , to such extent as may not affect the normal going of the match . given that some players put down words on their inner vests that are likely to invoke controversies , no writings will be allowed on the inner vests , starting from july 1 this year . fifa allowed advertisements on the team shirts , but only on their front side .
suicide bombing in jerusalem
xinhua news agency report of march 17 from jerusalem ( by staff reporters zhong cuihua and nie xiaoyang ) - a man set off explosives he carried near a bus at a neighborhood in northern jerusalem , killing himself immediately and slightly wounding another nine , who were rushed to hospital .
police have now sealed off the spot .
less than two hours earlier , a palestinian took on a shooting spree on passengers in the town of kfar saba in northern israel .
according to latest reports , a 16 - year-old israeli girl was killed and at least 12 others were wounded .
the gunman was shot dead by the police .
no organization has claimed responsibility for the attacks so far .
the prime minister office of israel has denounced the shooting attack .
israeli prime minister sharon said on the same day that despite the ongoing effort to negotiate a cease-fire with palestinians , israel would react to any attacks .
calligraphy and painting contest by civil servants to celebrate the 5th anniversary of hong kong 's return
xinhua news agency report of march 18 from hangzhou - a calligraphy and painting contest under the theme of " state civil servants --- the people 's servants " will be held among the civil servants in hong kong , macao and the mainland civil servants to celebrate the 5th anniversary of hong kong 's return and the promulgation of the first rules of conduct for state civil servants .
the contest was organized by the hong kong wen hui po , the mayor 's association of china and the leisure & cultural services department of the hong kong special administrative region government .
civil servants participating in the contest will create chinese paintings depicting the scenery of china as well as poems and songs . they will also adopt the general rules of conduct for civil servants , proverbs and idioms as content of their creations in the hope of promoting professionalism of civil servants such as duty of diligence , honesty and integrity and improving their self-cultivation and professional capability .
the contest is expected to highlight the atmosphere of festivity around the 5th anniversary of hong kong 's return and demonstrate the glamour of chinese calligraphy and paintings .
it is learned that the deadline for submission of works is april 20 , 2002 .
following the review process , the award-winning works will be compiled and published on the day of the 5th anniversary of hong kong 's return .
anc opposes sanctions against zimbabwe
xinhua new agency report of march 18 from johannesburg ( by staff reporter gao yuan ) - mortrant , secretary general of african national congress ( anc ) , south africa 's ruling party , lashed out at western countries like united states and united kingdom on march 18 , alleging they attempted to force zimbabwe to follow their will by way of sanctions .
in response to western countries ' threat of sanctions against zimbabwe , mortrant told the press : " who should rule zimbabwe is a matter of the zimbabwean people and should not be decided by western countries . "
he pointed out that mutual respect of national sovereignty is an international norm that every country should observe and the anc strongly objects to sanctions by western countries against a sovereign country .
mortrant said the sanction by western countries against zimbabwe would do no good but simply aggravate the social unrest of zimbabwe .
he called for cooperation between the zimbabwean government and the opposition parties to overcome the difficulties like food shortage and land crisis .
he stressed that only unity can foil any attempt to break up zimbabwe .
the anc issued a statement earlier calling for the international community to respect the choice of the zimbabwean people and help them through the plight .
zimbabwean president mugabe was reelected at the presidential election held from march 9 to 11 , but western countries , alleging serious cheatings and lack of fairness and freedom in the election , refused to recognize the election results and threatened further sanctions against zimbabwe .
so far , some western countries have declared ending economic aid to zimbabwe .
european union countries had lodged " selective " sanctions against zimbabwe before the election started on the ground that the zimbabwean government restricted press freedom and obstructed supervision .
honored french athletes back to paris from winter paralympics
xinhua new agency report of march 18 from paris ( by staff reporter wang jincheng ) - french athletes who participated in the salt lake city winter paralympics in united states returned to paris today .
they were warmly greeted at the de gaulle airport by french sports minster buffet , the representative of minister for the family , children and the disabled , s . royale , and other related figures .
the french delegation to the 8th winter paralympics held in salt lake city of united states won 19 medals , with its female athletes achieving 9 medals including a gold and the male athletes winning 10 medals including one gold .
this is the best performance the french delegation to winter paralympics has ever achieved .
s . royale said at the greeting ceremony that french athletes changed their social image with their outstanding performance and french people thanked them for their contribution in the struggle to change social impression of the disabled .
minister buffet said the french government would continue to support sports activities of the disabled .
jordan to return from injury on sunday at the earliest
xinhua new agency report of march 19 from washington d . c . ( by staff reporter xie peilin ) -- " air " jordan is likely to return on sunday at the earliest from a right knee surgery , but the washington wizards look hard to make it to the playoff games with the regular season drawing to a close .
washington wizards coach collins revealed today that jordan has geared up for some rehabilitative warm-ups and would be very likely to play the out-of-shape raptors on sunday in toronto , although he is still not in the mood for a return either on wednesday in denver or on thursday in salt lake city .
collins said , " he may return to action at any time . all depends on his own feeling .
his training focuses on defence at present , in addition to some shooting practice .
he is prepared to have harder training to see if his body responds well .
as far as the knee is concerned , he said he is at least 100 per cent better than before the surgery . "
jordan averaged 24.3 points this season . the team ended up with 4 wins and 8 losses during the three weeks after he had the surgery .
at present , with 15 games left for the regular season , the wizards are ranked 10th with 31 wins and 36 losses , trailing the miami heat by half a match and one match ahead of the raptors , but two and a half matches behind the 8th-ranked charlotte hornets .
coach collins , naturally , hopes jordan may return to lead the team to go farther , at least to win in a run soon to keep alive their dream of entering the playoffs .
collins said : " we 'd have had at least three more wins if jordan had not been injured .
as far as current situation is concerned , he is definitely capable of reactivating the team . "
korea to signal wish for resumption of talks with dprk
xinhua news agency report of march 19 from seoul ( by staff reporter zhang li ) -- the republic of korea government has asked indonesian president megawati to communicate president kim dae-jung 's wish to resume talks between the two koreas and between the united states and dprk as soon as possible to dprk 's leader kim jong il , the korean united news agency reported .
a korean government official said the message was that both the republic of korea and the united states wish to resolve the issues through dialogues , and urge dpr korea to take a more positive attitude .
indonesian president megawati is scheduled to visit dpr korea from march 28 to 30 and then visit korea from march 30 to april 1 , according to the report .
the korean government has forwarded this message to the indonesian side through diplomatic channels .
the korean government denied a news report of japan 's asahi shimbun that megawati will present kim jong ii with a letter handwritten by kim dae-jung .
ecb official : euro zone economic rebound to speed up within the year
xinhua new agency report of march 20 from brussels ( by staff reporter wang xingqiao ) - european central bank 's chief economist , dr. issing said here today that economy of the euro zone has crept out of the valley and will rebound in a speedy manner within the year .
issing was making the remarks at a hearing held by the council of the european union in belgium .
he said latest statistics indicate that the economy of the euro zone has grown steadily since early this year and the recovery is expected to speed up within the year .
the economic growth rate of the euro zone for this year is estimated to reach 2 - 2.5 percent .
issing ascribed the economic recovery mainly to growth in consumption and the already low level of inventory in the euro zone .
as to inflation , issing said the inflation rate in the euro zone is on the decline and there is no signs of risks of instability at the middle stage of economic development .
speaking of the world energy resources , issing noted that the recent price rise in the world oil market has upset decision makers worldwide and may have an impact on economic growth in the long run , which cannot be underestimated .
hong kong police detects first internet drug trafficking case
xinhua news agency report of march 21 from hong kong - hong kong police recently uncovered drug trafficking via the internet .
hong kong police 's narcotics bureau pointed out it was the first case in its kind and shall give rise to full attention .
hong kong police noted that in the past year several cases were found involving hong kong residents who bought narcotics such as head-swinging pills via the internet using credit cards .
the drug dealers buy drugs from thailand and then mail them to drug users in hong kong .
the several cases found last year mainly feature purchases via the internet with credit cards , according to kenny ip lau-chuen , chief superintendent of the narcotics investigation branch of hong kong police headquarters .
the hong kong police is now in cooperation with related units to crack down on such new types of crimes .
a chief officer from the united nations narcotics commission pointed out at a symposium on cross-territory organized crime held recently in hong kong that internet drug trafficking would pose a new challenge to law enforcers in the future .
the security bureau of the hong kong special administrative region completed consultancy on computer-related crimes last year and will amend legal rules to crack down on crimes using computers .
african college students call for africa not to become " peripheral area " of new technology
xinhua news agency report of march 21 from abidjan ( by staff reporter song nan ) - college students attending the second college forum of africa opened on the 21st called on african young people to make the best out of high technology in information and telecommunication areas to meet the challenge of economic globalization and prevent africa from becoming the " peripheral area " of new technology .
the chairperson of the forum noted in his speech that high technology has boosted economic development of countries in asia , europe and america .
the arrival of a new century has brought to africa many opportunities as well as challenges and the african young people should endeavour to master high technology to make their contribution to africa for a better tomorrow .
the topic of this year 's college forum of africa is : " new technology , information and exchange bring more opportunities for the cultivation of african talents . "
experts from dozens of african colleges and companies held discussions during the 3 - day conference on such topics as " africa 's future and challenge of new technology " , " cultural diversity and economic development " , " opportunities and prospect brought by e-commerce to africa " .
large-scale campus culture exhibitions will also be held during the forum .
indonesia reiterates opposition to garrisoning foreign armies
xinhua news agency report of march 22 from jakarta ( by staff reporter mai tangyuan ) - indonesian foreign ministry reiterated its opposition to garrisoning foreign armies in this island country in a statement issued on the 22nd .
the indonesian foreign ministry was reiterating its stance in response to a news report of usa today that the united states was contemplating sending troops to indonesia to help crack down on the al qaeda members fleeing afghanistan to indonesia .
the us government has never officially made any such request to the indonesian government , which can be confirmed by the later denial of such reports by the white house and the us department of defence , the statement said .
the statement reiterated that indonesia adopts the foreign policy based on the principles of independence and positiveness , saying it has been in close cooperation with countries like the us in the campaign against terrorism and is willing to continue cooperation in this respect .
ukraine condemns us interference in its internal affairs
xinhua news agency report of march 22 from kiev ( by staff reporter zhang zhiqiang ) - ukraine president kuchma addressed the press on the 22nd on the interference by the us house of representatives in ukraine 's internal affairs , saying its resolution was an unprecedented incident that was " perplexing " .
the us house of representatives passed a resolution on the 20th on the upcoming parliamentary election of ukraine , calling for a transparent , free and fair election on the 31st this month .
the resolution also requested ukraine government to execute the parliamentary election law to the letter , noting that the election results shall indicate whether ukraine is willing to proceed with the democratic reform .
kuchma said : " ukraine people are not a football subject to the playing of others . they have their deserved respect . "
kuchma also expressed thanks to rockinsky , chairman of the international ukrainian conference , for his letter to us congress .
rockinsky said in the letter : " look at what you did yourself .
do your homework before teaching others a lesson . "
leader of the ukrainian communist party symonenko said on the same day that the us act was brazen interference in ukraine 's internal affairs and a threat to ukraine 's independence .
ukraine united social-democratic party leader filenko said the biased comments of the us congress resolution on ukraine elections would split ukraine 's politic powers .
a spokesman for the foreign ministry of ukraine said on the 22nd that it was purely ukrainian people 's own matters to elect the state legislature and the local legislatures .
it was hoped that every country take a prudent attitude in accordance with the principles of international law and not to interfere with other countries ' internal affairs at the final stage of ukraine 's parliamentary election .
arab nations universally oppose us attack on iraq
xinhua new agency report of march 23 from riyadh - lebanon president lahoud told local newspaper riyadh daily that the leaders of arab countries have taken a unified stance against us attack on iraq before the opening of the arab summit , according to the march 23rd issue of the newspaper .
lahoud pointed out that no arab country permits us or its allies to attack any arab country in the absence of reasonable grounds and us must understand the consequence of such attacks under whatsoever pretexts .
lahoud said striking terrorism or " axis of evil " was an appealing pretext to influence western public opinion , but should not be used to carry out criminal acts .
he also urged us not to adopt double standards to strike terrorism in one place while ignoring israel 's national terrorism in another .
( in brief ) senior rok official to visit dprk in april
xinhua news agency report of march 25 from beijing - a spokesman for the republic of korea president announced in seoul on the 25th that president kim dae-jung 's special advisor for foreign affairs , security and reunification lim dong-won is to visit the dpr korea before the first week of april to discuss with dprk officials on mutual visits of separated families from the north and south as well as on how to ease tension between the two sides of the korean peninsula .
the spokesman said rok hopes the talks would " lay foundation " for the resumption of north-south relations , but she did not go to details of the talks .
she said the content of the talks would be made public after lim dong-won returns from dprk .
meanwhile , the central news agency of dprk also released a brief statement on the same day that president kim dae-jung 's special envoy will visit dprk .
the statement noted that the two sides would hold talks over the " serious conditions " on the korean peninsula as well as issues of mutual interest .
indonesian parliament speaker stands trial
xinhua news agency report of march 25 from beijing - indonesian parliament speaker akbar tandjung stood on trial on the 25th before a court in jakarta on charges of corruption and dereliction of duty , according to news received here .
tandjung was accused of misusing funds worth 3.8 million us dollars from the state food agency .
these funds have allegedly been used for the political party tandjung led , golkar , in its elections in 1999 .
these relief funds were originally reserved for the families impoverished by the financial crisis , but have never reached these families , the investigators found .
tandjung , however , has denied all the charges .
analysts said that whatsoever the judgement may be , this incident would probably cut tandjung 's chances of winning the presidency of indonesia .
" endeavor " launch delayed for robotic arm breakdown
xinhua news agency report of march 25 from washington d . c . - nasa announced on the 25th that the launch of space shuttle " endeavor " would be delayed from may 6 to 31 due to a technical breakdown in the canada-made robotic arm at the international space station .
" endeavor " is reported to carry seven astronauts to the international space station to carry out an 11 - day space mission .
the 7 - memeber crew includes astronauts from france and russia .
a nasa spokesman said the crew at the international space station might use the intervening time to solve the problems , but delay of the launch also meant they would have to wait in patience for three more weeks until amercan astronaut peggy whitson and two other russian astronauts arrive to replace them .
philip perry , the first non-russian european astronaut from france to fly to the space station , will carry out two space walks shortly after the mission begins .
shell 's investment in china to hit usd5 billion in 3 years
xinhua news agency report of march 26 from beijing ( by staff reporter qian chunxuan ) - shell oil chairman and president steve miller said the other day that shell oil 's total investment in china will be reaching 5 billion us dollars by the year of 2005 .
he made the remarks at the china development forum held in beijing , saying that shell 's investment in china amounts to 1.6 billion us dollars at present and will reach 5 billion dollars by 2005 including some currently-planed projects .
it was revealed that shell is now in negotiation with its chinese counterparts over a range of cooperative projects .
a joint venture with sinopec to build and operate 500 gas stations in jiangsu is expected to start off this year .
steve miller said that shell oil has engaged in china for over 100 years .
for shell oil , china holds a significant position in its global strategy with its huge market potential .
with the development of its economy , china 's oil consumption is expected to double by 2020 , amounting to 16 per cent of the total energy consumption of the world at that time .
china faces serious challenge of energy resources that makes it extremely important to diversify its energy sources to ensure energy security and protect the environment . shell oil would play an important role in such a process .
xinhua news agency report of march 26 from the united nations ( by staff reporter gu zhenqiu ) - a united nations spokesman announced on the 26th a security council delegation will leave on april 27 to visit congo and other african countries involved in the congo conflict to inject the congo peace process with new energy .
the spokesman said the delegation , headed by levitte , french ambassador at un , consists of representatives from the 15 member countries of the security council .
this visit is aimed to have dialogues with leaders of the rival powers in the congo conflict to urge them to abide by the peace deals they signed in 1999 in the zambian capital of lusaka .
this is the third time since may 2000 that the security council sent delegations to visit the african lake area .
sri lanka government to hold peace talks with tiger rebels
xinhua news agency report of march 27 from colombo ( by staff reporter zhang yadong ) - the sri lanka government announced on the 27th that they plan to hold peace talks with the anti-government liberation tigers of tamil eelam ( ltte ) in the hope of putting an end to the nearly 20 - year-long bloody ethnical conflicts in the country .
peiris , minister of justice , constitution , ethnic affairs and national integration told a press conference on the same day that the sri lanka government and ltte had agreed to hold peace talks soon and the government wishes the talks to begin from the first week of may .
he said initial talks were preparatory for the subsequent material talks .
the sri lanka government is yet to disclose the venue of meetings , but news reports said talks would be held in thailand .
peiris said the government plans to hold talks with ltte in an asian country and has made related preparations .
reports also said the chief negotiator of ltte , balasingham , who returned to the ltte-controlled northern part of sri lanka from his three-year exile in london , and prabhakaran , the ltte leader , held talks the other day with norwegian special envoy solheim and norwegian ambassador to sri lanka in northern sri lanka .
after the talks , ltte agreed to resume peace talks with the government when order returns to the territory under its control , but insisted the government release the injunction against them before the coming talks .
the sri lanka government and ltte signed a permanent cease-fire agreement in february this year , laying foundation for talks between them .
china unicom net profit up 38 % last year
xinhua news agency report of march 27 from hong kong ( by staff reporter li kai ) - china unicom company limited , which is listed in the hong kong stock exchange , announced it achieved across-the-board good performance last year , making a net profit of rmb4.457 billion , up nearly 38 percent over the previous year .
one of the comprehensive telecommunication operators in china , china unicom provides services in the sectors of mobile telecommunication , domestic and international long distance calls , data , internet and paging .
china unicom declared that the total amount of service time of long distance calls via switch boards and ip phone calls last year reached 6.41 billion minutes , 5.9 times more than the previous year . the market share increased from 1.3 percent in 2000 to 7.7 percent and the total time for the incoming service of international phone calls rose by 3.4 times .
yang xianzu , ceo of china unicom , said the company would speed up development of mobile telecommunication services this year and take on a strategy of differentiation to ensure development of mobile services in cdma and gsm to attract more customers of mobile phones .
central banks of china and japan signed agreement on currency exchange
xinhua news agency report of march 28 from tokyo ( by staff reporter wang yan ) - dai xiangling , governor of the people 's bank of china , signed an agreement on currency exchange with masaru hayami , governor of bank of japan , on the 28th in tokyo .
according to the agreement , the people 's bank of china and bank of japan may provide each other with a currency portfolio of 3 billion us dollars when necessary to help stabilize the financial market .
the signing of currency exchange agreement between china and japan indicated further advancement of cooperation between central banks of the two countries .
this agreement between china and japan is the second of its kind since the people 's bank of china and bank of thailand signed such an agreement for a portfolio of 2 billion us dollars .
china is expected to sign such agreement with other countries like the republic of korea .
dai xianglong said china would take an active role in financial cooperation in asia and would like to make its own contribution to the regional economy , financial stability and prevention of risks along with other asian countries .
wu dawei , china 's ambassador to japan , was present at the signing ceremony of the currency exchange agreement between the people 's bank of china and bank of japan .
afghans begin restoring home after quake
xinhua news agency report of march 28 from kabul ( by staff reporter pan yunzhao ) - people suffering from an earthquake in afghanistan 's northern province of baghlan began to restore their homes three days after the disaster hit .
rebecca , spokeswoman for the un office for coordination of humanitarian affairs to afghanistan , told xinhua news agency that a central group jointly organized by the afghan interim government , the un agencies and non-governmental organizations found during its investigation and assessment of the quake-hit areas on the 28th that the inhabitants there have begun restoring their houses , some using relief materials provided by aid agencies .
she said , in light of the circumstances , the un aid agencies have begun considering to help the quake-hit inhabitants to restore their homes .
at present , aid agencies are distributing to the suffered inhabitants relief materials they have stored in quantity in the quake-hit areas by air-dropping and direct allocation .
a severe earthquake struck the districts of nahrin and berhga in the province of baghlan on the 25th , causing heavy casualties and tens of thousands of people homeless .
japan suspends humanitarian aid to russia
xinhua news agency report of march 29 from tokyo - japanese foreign minister yoriko kawaguchi announced on the 29th that japan would suspend humanitarian aid to russian until after completing reform of the international committee responsible for the aid programs .
yoriko kawaguchi said that with exception to labor costs for the operation of the committee and a technological cooperation aid program to russia , the japanese government would control aid funds to russia through this committee until reform of it is completed .
this decision was made in response to the recent remarks made by japan 's minister of finance , masajuro shiokawa .
masajuro shiokawa recently called for cabinet members to ensure each portion of fund of the government be properly used given the continued deteriorating of japan 's domestic financial conditions .
it is learned that the committee has been accused of dereliction of duty and being not transparent enough about the using of funds after it was revealed that the deputy chief cabinet secretary muneo suzuki has imposed undue pressure upon the ministry of foreign affairs to influence the application procedure of aid programs to russia .
eu to negotiate with china on temporary protection measures on steel imports
xinhua news agency report of march 29 from beijing ( by staff reporter che yuming ) - minister of foreign trade and economics cooperation shi guangsheng said here today that the european union has , in clear response to china 's concern over eu implementing temporary protection measures against some steel imports , said it would start negotiations with china soon and would grant special arrangements to china as a developing country to properly resolve this issue .
shi guangsheng was answering questions from journalists at the national working conference on foreign economics and trade law .
he said the ever-fiercer trade war on steel was originating from the united states .
at present , all parties concerned have denounced the section 201 of us and requested bilateral negotiations , some of them even proposing settlement through the dispute settlement mechanism of the world trade organization .
in response to eu 's decision on march 27 to take temporary protection measures against steel imports from 15 countries , shi guangsheng expressed his serious concern over the issue the same day in a letter to eu trade commissioner lamy and proposed bilateral negotiations with eu .
truck , train clash kills 7 in liaoning
xinhua news agency report of march 30 from shenyang ( staff reporter wang jun ) - a train collided with a truck at 14 : 13 on march 29 in the city of jinzhou of liaoning province , killing 7 and seriously wounding 3 .
a four-wheeled industrial truck collided with a train running from jinzhou to chengde while the truck was attempting to outrun the train through a crossing between lijiagou and the district of zhoujiatun in yi county of jinzhou , according to the safety inspection office of the bureau of shenyang railways .
the truck was loaded with 50 bags of chemical fertilizer and seeds as well as 14 persons in violation of rules at that time .
four persons escaped without injury by jumping out of the truck at the time of collision while other 10 were either killed or wounded . the railings at the crossing was destroyed and the locomotive of the train also sustained damage to an extent .
after the accident occurred , the ministry of railways , bureau of shenyang railways and local government officials have rushed to the scene to handle relief issues .
council of the league of arab states ( las ) discussed palestinian situation at an emergency conference today at its headquarters .
representatives of 22 arab countries to las were present at the conference .
moussa told the press conference held after the conference closed that the escalation of israeli military campaign against palestine was clear indication of israel 's rejection of peace .
what is going on is continuation of israel 's military occupation of palestine and the palestinian people will continue their resistance against israeli invasion .
he said , " the palestinian people 's resistance will continue as long as the israeli military occupation of palestinian territory continues and israeli tanks and soldiers remain in the palestinian territory . "
xinhua news agency report of march 31 from jerusalem ( by staff reporter zhong cuihua , nie xiaoyang ) - israel 's security cabinet decided on the 31st to intensify military attacks on the palestinian-controlled territory and to advance a series of planed military actions .
israeli prime minister sharon convened his core ministers in the afternoon of the same day to discuss current israeli-palestinian situations and how to cope with the increasing number of bomb attacks by palestinians . it was decided to intensify military attacks on palestinians .
political sources here disclosed that the security cabinet believed that intensifying attacks on palestinians may curb , but would not eradicate terrorist actions .
sharon is expected to explain the government 's stand in handling the conflict between palestine and israel in a televised address to the country at 8 : 30 p.m. local time ( 1 : 30 , april 1 beijing time ) .
cambodia , vietnam jointly hold commodity fair
xinhua news agency report of april 1 from phnom penh ( by staff reporter yan ming ) - a commodity fair jointly held by vietnam and cambodia opened on the 1st here , with up to 200 sorts of commodities on display .
fifty companies from cambodia and vietnam participated in the fair with 55 booths .
commodities on display include motor vehicles , electronic appliances , agricultural tools , medicine , beverage , food and ready-to-wear clothing .
vietnam 's ambassador to cambodia nguyen duy hung noted at the opening ceremony that there is great potential in economic and trade development between vietnam and cambodia and commodity fairs may serve to promote economic and trade cooperation and exchange between the two countries .
he said trade between the two countries have made encouraging progress in recent years , with trade volume increasing from us $ 16.9 million in 2000 to 18 million in 2001 .
cambodian trade minister cham prasidh said it was a good thing for cambodia and vietnam to unite to develop economy and trade of the two countries , which would promote economic development of asean countries and get the two countries integrated into asean and world economy soon .
indonesian badminton experts : taufik 's ranking a big advantage
xinhua new agency report of april 1 from jakarta ( by staff reporter mai tangyuan ) - kutuzi badminton club chairman arisantos told antara news agency in the capital city of semarang of central java on the 1st that male shuttler taufik 's world ranking will be a big advantage for the indonesian team to defend its championship at the thomas cup tournament .
he said taufik 's current ranking of 33rd may place him as the team 's second or third-ranked singles player , which means less pressure on him than as the leading player .
in team events , the leading player 's victory may have influence on the subsequent matches , at least on teammates psychologically and push them to go all out for victories .
however , in case that indonesia 's top-ranked singles player tumbles , taufik as the second or third-ranked player is expected to chalk up a victory , thus subjecting the final win to the two double matches .
he believed that taufik 's return has increased indonesia 's chances of defending its thomas cup , because this young man is a very excellent player in the world .
he believed that taufik 's return brings hopes to indonesia of beating its opponents including host china .
a report said that in a poll conducted on an indonesian badminton website , 45 percent of the polled believed the indonesian team can defend the thomas cup , 21 percent voted for the chinese , while 17 percent favored malaysia .
georgian troops to withdraw from kodori gorge
xinhua news agency report of april 2 from tbilisi - special representatives from the united nations and representatives from georgia , abkhazia and the commonwealth of independent states signed an agreement in tbilisi on the 2nd to withdraw georgian troops from the kodori gorge .
russia tass news agency reported that the agreement stipulated that georgian troops shall retreat from the kodori gorge by april 10 while peacekeeping force and un observers shall resume patrolling of this area , and that all parties should ensure safety of residents in this area .
boden , un secretary general 's special representative to georgia , said the agreement was a " good signal " that georgia and abkhazia are willing to settle their conflict on the basis of mutual compromise .
he said this document would clear the way for further talks .
the independence-claiming abkhazia authorities in the territory of georgia went into military conflict with the georgian government in 1992 .
conflicts between the two sides broke out again last october in kodori gorge and georgia sent its troops there shortly afterwards .
xinhua news agency report of april 2 from ankara ( by staff reporter huai chengbo ) - according to anadolu news agency reports , turkey 's foreign minister cem said on the 2nd at a convention of turkey 's parliament to discuss israel 's invasion into the palestinian territory in west bank of jordan river that the madrid mideast peace vision which constitutes the basis for mideast peace process needed a new beginning and proposed an international conference on mideast issues .
cem said that us should take action immediately to end the suffering and mutual killings of palestinians and israelis .
he stressed that the us must treat palestinians and israelis equally and bear its responsibility .
talking of turkey 's stance on the mideast issue , he said mideast is of great strategic significance to turkey and turkey hopes for peace and stability in this region .
he reiterated turkey 's support of the resolution on palestinian and israel conflict recently passed by the united nations security council .
this resolution called palestinians and israelis for cease-fire and israel to withdraw troops from ram-allah and other palestinian territories .
according to a separate report , turkey has made inquiries with palestine , israel and other mideast countries including egypt , saudi arabia and jordan on the convention of an international conference on the mideast issues and has held consultations with the us , russia and the european union .
the mideast peace conference held in spain 's capital city of madrid in 1990 laid down the principle of " land for peace " .
under guidance of this principle , palestine and israel signed a declaration in washington d . c . in 1993 on the interim self-government of palestine .
ntt telecommunication finances an internet company
xinhua news agency report of april 3 from tokyo - a spokesman for the ntt telecommunication corporation , a subsidiary of the nippon telecommunication and telephone company , said on the 3rd that the corporation will continue support of the business development of a us-based internet company , verio , by pumping us $ 30.5 million into the company .
the spokesman said they estimated at least us $ 30.5 million is needed this year to cover verio 's loss , and ntt is willing to pay the sum and plans to continue its financial support until it turns profitable .
it is learned that the colorado-based verio is a business-oriented internet service provider engaged in high-speed internet access , e-commerce , private network and maintenance of websites .
nippon telecommunication and telephone company bought the company for us $ 5.5 billion in 2000 .
during the past few years , ntt telecommunication corporation has injected us $ 2.16 billion in total into verio , which has kept running in red .
liberian anti-government forces close in on capital
xinhua news agency report of april 3rd from monrovia - liberian army announced that fighting between the liberian rebels and the government troops has escalated in the past week and extended on the night of the 3rd to the barracks of government forces merely 35 kilometres to the key military route toward the capital city of monrovia .
this distance is as far as when the rebels pushed to the town of clair on the outskirts of the capital in february this year .
the barracks are located at the pivotal town of dodi , the only route linking monrovia with the neighbouring countries of cote d ' ivoire and guinea .
the war erupted on the 28th last month when the un investigation group was investigating the liberian government 's trading of diamonds for arms against a backdrop of sanctions against liberia .
the liberians united for reconciliation and democracy ( lurd ) attempts to intensify its attack to overthrow the taylor government and force him to step down .
a senior official of the government troops said the lurd was launching the military attack in an attempt to take over the diamond mines because they need money to buy more arms and sustain its economy through difficulties .
the lurd rebels began war against liberia president taylor in 2000 .
xinhua news agency report of april 4 from united nations ( by staff reporter ding baozhong ) - un world food programme ( wfp ) executive director bertini said in new york on the 4th that wfp has become the largest humanitarian aid agency in the world , distributing us $ 1.7 billion worth of food in aid worldwide in 2001 .
bertini pointed out in an address to the un security council about the agency 's actions and role that wfp has lent a hand to disaster-hit areas and conflict-torn areas worldwide , saved numerous lives , made contributions to the renovation of many countries and the stability of regions in conflict .
she said wfp supplied us $ 240 million worth of food aid to afghanistan last year , benefiting millions of afghans .
bertini called for donating countries ' generosity to help wfp fulfil its mission to aid afghanistan in 2002 .
she also said that only us $ 70 million has been amassed so far , compared with the total sum of us $ 285 needed for the programme .
bertini also appealed to un agencies and the member countries for their attention to the safety of un staff on humanitarian missions and bring those criminals offending un staff to law .
statistics showed that a total number of 204 un workers have been killed since 1992 , with only 24 criminals arrested .
germany donated blocks of berlin wall to un
xinhua news agency report of april 5 from beijing - the german government donated three blocks of the berlin wall , symbol of the cold war between the west and the east , to united nations on the 4th .
according to foreign news agency reports , the three blocks are 3.6 meters high and weighs 2.8 tons each , decorated with an image of a man and a woman getting over the wall to hug each other .
the three wall blocks were transported to new york in october last year to mark the reunification of the two germanies in 1990 .
the public has been denied visit of the blocks at the un park located by the eastern river of new york which has been closed since the september 11 incident .
un secretary general anan said on the occasion that the ending of the split of west and east indicated " peace is always possible , even in the mideast . "
german parliament speaker thierse told anan that there had existed such a wall in the hearts of many before the berlin wall was erected .
berlin wall has become history from which not only germans can learn a lesson .
bill gates hoaxed on fool 's day
xinhua news agency report of april 5 from beijing - the well-known microsoft president bill gates was " hoaxed " by a canadian radio station on the april fool 's day .
mark antowan oden and sebastian trudell , both staffers for the ckmf-fm radio station in quebec of canada called bill gates on april 1 , claiming to be canadian prime minister chretien and alternately pretending the prime minister 's voice to have a 10 minute talk with bill gates .
the talks range from world economy to defects of the windows operating system and bill gates was invited to visit quebec at his convenience .
the recording of the talks was aired on the night of the 2nd in an entertainment programme and re-aired the following day at listeners ' request .
mark antowan oden said afterwards that he did not expect to have so easily got in contact with bill gates and his aids have not found this was merely a fool 's day hoax .
a microsoft spokesman , after learning of the truth , claimed the radio station convinced microsoft they were canadian government officials with some forged documents , warning the hoax , though " funny " , has gone sort of too far .
sources said the radio station once played hoax on fool 's day on other celebrities like celine dion .
xinhua news agency report of april 5 from ankara ( by staff reporter huai chengbo ) - interim afganistan president karzai called on the 5th in ankara for the multi-national peacekeeping forces in afghanistan to extend their activity out of the capital of kabul to other areas .
karzai told journalists at the airport after his two-day visit to turkey that afghans outside the capital of kabul has seen the extension of peacekeeping forces ' action as a guarantee of sustained peace in afghanistan .
earlier this year , karzai called for un security council to send more peacekeeping forces to other areas than the capital of kabul .
he said it would serve as a signal that the international community would take responsibility for a country torn by war for 23 years .
turkey has agreed in principle to accept the command of the afghan peacekeeping forces from britain .
however , turkey , worried about security in areas outside kabul , does not agree to extend the peacekeeping area .
the us has manifested its support of turkey 's stance .
karzai said on the 5th turkey 's worry about its troops involving into the tumult recurring in areas outside kabul was unnecessary
but he said the afghan government would accept whatever decision made by countries participating in the peacekeeping forces .
sandstorm attacks north china again
xinhua news agency report of april 6 from beijing ( by staff reporter dong jun ) - the central station of meteorology announced at 6 p.m. today that there will be sandstorms beginning tonight until tomorrow in the eastern part of northwest china , most of north china and the central and southern parts of northeast china due to a strong cold spell .
weather forecasts suggested sandstorms in central and southeastern inner mongolia , the northern parts of shaanxi , shanxi and hebei provinces , western liaoning and jilin provinces and strong sandstorms in some regions thereof ; floating dust and sand is expected in some areas of huanghuai region , accompanied by winds with forces of 5 to 7 scales and temperature falls by 6 to 12 degrees centigrade , or by over 14 in some areas .
it was sunny this morning in beijing , yet turned windy in the afternoon , driving people engaged in outdoor activities back home .
despite weather forecasts by the central station of meteorology yesterday evening that there will be strong winds in north china , many residents , refreshed by the good weather left by spring rain , went on outing early in the morning .
today , the inner mongolia 's capital city of hohhot was also hit by a spell of cold winds .
despite the strong northerly winds , the sky remains very clear .
experts said the spring rainfall yesterday in most parts of inner mongolia , with a precipitation of 33 millimetres in the city of hohhot , will not only greatly alleviate the drought but effectively hold off the attack of sandstorms .
china telecom market to surpass 1 trillion yuan in 2005
xinhua news agency report of april 6 from shanghai ( by staff reporter feng yizhen ) - officials from the ministry of information industry attending the sino-russian senior symposium on information and telecommunication disclosed that china 's telecommunication market will reach rmb1.05 trillion in value in 2005 , or 2.5 times that of 2000 .
it was estimated that china 's telephone users will increase by 26 percent annually in the 10th five-year period ( 2001 - 2005 ) , with 24 percent in eastern regions , 26 percent in central areas and 30 percent in western regions .
by 2005 , the number of telephone customers is to hit 500 million households , or 40 percent of the total households of the country .
china 's mobile telephone services are extending to ordinary customers and changing from the simple message communication services to data transmission , medium and high speed multimedia services , and high speed interactive multimedia services .
internet services remain the fastest growing sector of china 's telecommunication services , with the content extending from the narrow-banded to the broadbanded , the classified vod services extending to high speed interactive services and customers from large and medium-sized cities to central towns and cities .
during the 10th five-year period , china 's data and multimedia internet customers will grow by over 70 percent on an annual basis .
by 2005 , internet customers across the country is to reach 200 million .
annan to discuss mideast situation with us , russia and eu
xinhua news agency report of april 7 from madrid ( by staff reporter liu ruichang ) - spanish newspaper abesie reported on the 7th that un secretary general annan will hold talks on the 10th with us secretary of state powell , spanish foreign minister pique , who also serves as the current rotating chairman of eu , eu 's senior representative for foreign and security policy solana and russian foreign minister ivanov in the spanish capital of madrid , discussing solutions to the deteriorating conflict between israel and palestine .
annan made the disclosure during an interview with a reporter of the newspaper at the headquarters of un in new york .
abesie published the interview on the same day .
speaking of un 's role in mediating the military conflict between palestine and israel , annan said un has played an active part in the mediation of the conflict , passing two important resolutions numbered 1397 and 1402 on the conflict between palestine and israel .
he said he will talk with senior leaders from us , eu and russia when attending the conference in madrid and discuss the serious situation in mideast .
sources said annan will co-chair with spanish prime minister aznar the 2nd un world convention on ageing on the 8th in madrid ; powell is also scheduled to make an official visit to spain next week to renew the military cooperation treaty between us and spain ; ivanov is to fly to spain specifically for a meeting with powell to discuss bilateral relations .
computer crimes cost us billions of dollars last year
xinhua news agency report of april 7 from washington - increasingly rampant computer crimes cost us companies and government agencies billions of dollars last year , rising sharply over the previous year , according to a us report published on the 7th titled " 2001 : computer crimes and security investigation " .
there have occurred many a case across the country last year in which computer systems were attacked by viruses and rejection of service in addition to various security loopholes .
538 computer experts from the industry , government agencies and universities noted that us companies and other agencies pay dear for computer crimes each year .
although the precise loss is yet to be determined , 35 per cent of the agencies surveyed admitted to loss totaling over us $ 3.778 billion , a marginal increase over us $ 2.656 billion suffered in 2000 .
this report , compiled by american computer security association and federal bureau of investigation , has not provided assessment of losses sustained by persoanal computer users of the country .
berber language recognized as official language of algeria
xinhua news agency report of april 8 from algiers ( by staff reporter xu donghua ) - algerian parliament reviewed and passed a constitution amendment proposed by president bouteflika to recognize berber language as one of the country 's official languages on 8th at a joint convention of the two houses .
algerian president abdelaziz bouteflika said in a speech at the convention that the passing of the amendment affirmed the diversity of algerian culture through a legal manner and would contribute to the ethnical binding of algeria .
berbers are indigenous people to north africa and berbers inhabiting in algeria constitute one sixth of the total population of the country .
the algerian constitution named arabic as the only official language after independence , which was opposed by berbers .
serious social tumults broke out last april in the kabili area inbabited by berbers in eastern algeria .
more than 60 people were killed and 2000 wounded in the 3 - month-long tumult .
local people called for berber language to be recognized as official language of algeria by the constitution .
president bouteflika promised in a televised address to the country on march 21 this year to amend the constitution to satisfy berbers ' demand .
white house : israel 's withdrawal of troops from two cities in west bank only a beginning
xinhua news agency report of april 8 from washington d . c . - white house spokesman fleischer claimed in a statement on the night of 8th that israel 's withdrawal of troops from tulkarem and qalqilya on the west bank was merely a " beginning " , and all parties in mideast should fulfil their responsibilities .
fleischer said in a brief statement : " this is a beginning .
like what president bush said on the 4th , all parties in mideast should fulfil their responsibilities . president called for each party to make more effort . "
israeli troops began to pull out of tulkarem and qalqilya early 9th local time , but did not disclose when it would complete withdrawal from all other cities in west bank .
bush reiterated in an address to journalists in tennessee that israel must withdraw from the palestinian territory immediately , stressing that he " means it " .
bush said he 's already told israeli prime minister sharon of america 's request and is now waiting for israel 's immediate withdrawal of its troops .
bush says nato must establish new relationship with russia
xinhua news agency report of april 10 from beijing - local reports said us president bush said nato must establish a " new and constructive relationship " with russia during a meeting with nato secretary general solana .
bush said by establishing this relationship " we will resolve once and for good the disagreement left from the last era . "
bush discussed a lot of issues including iraq and nato 's eastern extension with robinson at the meeting .
bush said , " nato must build up new , versatile capabilities to meet the challenges of 21st century .
we must admit new members . "
bush did not directly refer to iraq in the press interview following the meeting .
but he said " we will consult with our allies when we engage in actions against terrorism . "
robinson said bush and he discussed " the threat faced by us in europe and north america , including weapons of massive destruction .
he said all nato member countries will unite to overcome these threats and achieve " success " .
mexican president 's visit of us and canada vetoed by senate
xinhua news agency report of april 9 from mexico city - a mexico senate spokesman said on the 9th that mexican president fox 's planned visit of us and canada in the middle of this month was vetoed by the senate .
this is the first time in the country 's history that the senate vetoed the president 's visit plan .
the spokesman said the senate vetoed the plan by 71 to 41 .
senators who vetoed the plan said the president should spend more energy on domestic matters rather than visiting foreign countries .
last year , president fox made 15 visits to foreign countries .
a senator said they vetoed the plan because one of the major goals of president fox 's visit is to meet with mexican immigrants .
reports said after being vetoed by senate , president fox 's visit plan is to be referred to the house of representatives for voting .
if vetoed again , his visit will be blown .
if passed , the plan will be returned to the senate for review .
president fox was originally planning to fly to seattle of us to meet with microsoft president bill gates and members of mexican immigrant communities .
afterwards , he is expected to fly to vancouver and calgary of canada to hold talks with local businessmen and academics before wrapping up the 3 - day visit .
west asian games track & field events start
xinhua news agency report of april 10 from kuwait ( by staff reporter an jiang ) - with the west asian games faring halfway , the track and field events , highlight of the games , finally got under way today .
athletes from 12 countries participating in the games will compete for gold medals in seven events on the first day of track and field competition .
in the ball events staged on the 9th , the kuwaiti basketball team won the championship by edging opponent qatar 97 - 93 .
syria finished third after beating iran 110 - 92 .
in football , kuwait has to beat the dark horse , palestine , today in order to win the championship .
this match was called by local media as " bottleneck match " that would decide the final results .
the syrian handball team , after beating iranians 33 - 32 , plays kuwait today for the gold medal .
as of the 9th , kuwait remained on top of the medal table with 49 medals , including 19 golds , 18 silvers and 12 bronzes , followed by iran , syria , saudi arabia , qatar and jordan .
powell : meeting with arafat very important
xinhua news agency report of april 10 from madrid - us secretary of state powell said on the 10th here his meeting with palestinian leader arafat during his visit to the mideast is " very important " and he hoped there will be no difficulty in arranging meeting with arafat .
powell made the remarks after meeting with officials from eu , russia and un .
he said , " arafat is the leader of palestinian people . i think the palestinian people and leaders of arab countries believe he is the person israel has to deal with . "
reports said us white house spokesman fleischer said the same day that israel has promised us that powell may meet with arafat during his visit to the mideast .
israel defence minister binyamin ben eliezer told journalists the same day in the city of jenin on west bank of jordan river that israel would not hinder powell 's meeting with arafat late this week .
powell 's mediation mission to the mideast originally did not include a meeting with arafat .
palestinian officials once said if powell refused meeting with arafat , no palestinian representatives would have talks with him .
leaders of the arab nations also reiterated during powell 's visit to morocco and egypt that his visit would end up with no results without meeting arafat .
former serbian interior minister of yugoslavia attempts suicide
xinhua news agency report of april 11 from belgrade ( by staff reporter yang chengming ) - vlajko stojiljkovic , former serbian interior minister of federal republic of yugoslavia and incumbent member of parliament who is wanted by the hague tribunal as war crime suspect , shot himself in the head outside the parliament building during the night of 11th .
he was rushed to hospital immediately and now remains in danger .
stojiljkovic said in his suicide note that " as a member of the federal parliament , i take this action as protest against this puppet regime .
i denounce their ruthless violation of the constitution and laws of the federal republic of yugoslavia , their damage of the dignity of the country to destroy the country . "
yugoslav president kostunica described the suicide attempt in a statement made later in the day as a warning to the western countries that constantly set conditions and pressures on yugoslavia .
yugoslav federal parliament and house of citizens respectively passed a law on the 10th and 11th on cooperation with the hague tribunal .
the law stipulates that war crime suspects who were wanted by the hague tribunal before the passing of the law will be extradited to the hague tribunal whenever he is found in the territory of yugoslavia and whatsoever citizenship he holds .
according to the law , stojiljkovic is also to be extradited to hague .
saudi arabia backs palestine with donations
xinhua news agency report of april 12 from riyadh ( by staff reporter yu kaiyuan ) - saudi arabia began nationwide donation from 4 pm 11th to 3 am 12th local time to support palestine .
